00:20:13.462 --> 00:20:15.047
No. Come on. I'm tall.

457
00:20:15.130 --> 00:20:17.966
We have so many similarities to a T.

458
00:20:18.050 --> 00:20:19.760
We can just sit down right here.

459
00:20:21.678 --> 00:20:24.765
-This is nice.
-[Hayley] This is so fun.

460
00:20:24.848 --> 00:20:27.726
-[David] You want my jacket?
-Wow. Thank you.

461
00:20:27.809 --> 00:20:30.354
So I'm just figuring out
who I think would be

462
00:20:30.437 --> 00:20:34.233
a great Trial Marriage partner
for me in my experience.

463
00:20:34.316 --> 00:20:36.276
-What's your worst fear in marriage?
-[music fades]

464
00:20:36.860 --> 00:20:39.154
-Them leaving.
-Okay.

465
00:20:39.238 --> 00:20:41.198
Them getting up and just leaving.
You know?

466
00:20:41.865 --> 00:20:44.159
Had a lot of people
come in my life and leave.

467
00:20:44.243 --> 00:20:46.328
With my ex-partner. Casey.

468
00:20:46.411 --> 00:20:48.580
that sense of fear is still there
because it is possible.

469
00:20:49.414 --> 00:20:52.042
-You know?
-Mm-hm. That's true.

470
00:20:52.125 --> 00:20:53.210
-100%.
-Mm-hm.

471
00:20:53.794 --> 00:20:56.588
But you were issued The Ultimatum.
so you're not ready. right?

472
00:20:56.672 --> 00:20:58.590
Because of something
that someone else is doing.

473
00:20:58.674 --> 00:21:00.842
-Oh. okay.
-[pensive music playing]

474
00:21:00.926 --> 00:21:04.930
-There's something I'm missing.
-Something that-- Okay. yeah.

475
00:21:05.013 --> 00:21:06.765
That is not allowing me

476
00:21:06.848 --> 00:21:10.811
to fully invest myself
and take that next step.

477
00:21:11.395 --> 00:21:12.813
-You know?
-Yeah.

478
00:21:13.397 --> 00:21:15.649
-That's hard.
-What would that be? But what is it?

479
00:21:15.732 --> 00:21:18.277
-It's the emotional side of it.
-The emotional-- Yeah. I know.

480
00:21:18.360 --> 00:21:19.861
That's what I want.

481
00:21:19.945 --> 00:21:22.572
So it's like.
if you can't give me that. then…

482
00:21:23.323 --> 00:21:25.367
You know. Yeah.

483
00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:28.453
Anything you want to know.
anything you're curious about.

484
00:21:28.537 --> 00:21:30.914
living with a Trial Marriage partner?

485
00:21:31.498 --> 00:21:32.582
How do you give love?

486
00:21:32.666 --> 00:21:35.752
I'm very affectionate.
so I like to touch. for sure.

487
00:21:35.836 --> 00:21:38.505
I like the touch. You?
What's one of your love languages?

488
00:21:38.588 --> 00:21:42.134
-One? I literally have all of them.
-Stop. Oh. you're that perfect?

489
00:21:42.217 --> 00:21:44.511
-[both laugh]
-I'm serious. I give all of them.

490
00:21:44.594 --> 00:21:46.054
-I knew it.
-I'm serious.

491
00:21:46.138 --> 00:21:51.560
♪ You must be the right time
Right place to fall in… ♪

492
00:21:51.643 --> 00:21:54.604
What about physical?
What would turn you on?

493
00:21:54.688 --> 00:21:56.982
♪ Can you be the one… ♪

494
00:21:57.566 --> 00:22:02.029
Like. what gets you. like…
just blood flowing. you know?

495
00:22:02.112 --> 00:22:03.030
Hot and bothered.

496
00:22:03.113 --> 00:22:04.906
Biting's one.

497
00:22:04.990 --> 00:22:08.827
-Ooh. no way. No way.
-Oh my gosh. [laughs]

498
00:22:08.910 --> 00:22:11.121
-Yeah.
-That's one of mine too. Definitely.

499
00:22:11.204 --> 00:22:13.457
-I don't know if I've said that out loud.
-That's funny.

500
00:22:13.540 --> 00:22:15.625
I don't think
I ever told anyone that either.

501
00:22:15.709 --> 00:22:17.210
[laughing] Oh my gosh.

502
00:22:18.086 --> 00:22:19.254
♪ Be the one… ♪

503
00:22:19.338 --> 00:22:21.006
Okay. deep question.

504
00:22:21.715 --> 00:22:23.300
-Oh stop!
-[both laughing]

505
00:22:23.383 --> 00:22:25.844
♪ Be my one ♪

506
00:22:25.927 --> 00:22:28.472
[David] I love this view right here.
It is beautiful though.

507
00:22:28.555 --> 00:22:33.518
What'd you say would be the hardest thing
you've ever gone through in life?

508
00:22:33.602 --> 00:22:36.313
-Losing my stepdad.
-Mm-hm.

509
00:22:37.314 --> 00:22:42.527
Just because. like. after that happened.
my whole life changed.

510
00:22:42.611 --> 00:22:44.196
[poignant music playing]

511
00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:47.574
When my stepdad died. CPS got involved.

512
00:22:48.367 --> 00:22:50.535
And then I went to live
with my dad in Dallas.

513
00:22:50.619 --> 00:22:53.580
And that was. like.
such a low point in my life.

514
00:22:53.663 --> 00:22:54.498
Yeah.

515
00:22:54.581 --> 00:22:58.710
Just because you go from not having
a relationship with your father. ever…

516
00:22:58.794 --> 00:23:02.005
It was definitely
that feeling of feeling lost and. like.

517
00:23:02.089 --> 00:23:03.673
just going through the motions.

518
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:09.262
just because I didn't have a set space
or. like. an "identity." you know?

519
00:23:09.346 --> 00:23:10.806
-In high school.
-I get you 100%.

520
00:23:10.889 --> 00:23:11.723
You know?

521
00:23:11.807 --> 00:23:16.812
I get it. I understand because. you know.
I was raised by my stepfather too.

522
00:23:16.895 --> 00:23:19.981
Like. my dad didn't teach me
how to be a man. My stepfather did.

523
00:23:20.065 --> 00:23:21.441
And then he had heart problems.

524
00:23:21.525 --> 00:23:24.277
Being there and taking him.
like. every day.

525
00:23:24.361 --> 00:23:26.780
Showering him.
lifting him up. and feeding him

526
00:23:26.863 --> 00:23:29.699
and making sure he's good.
that was one of the hardest things.

527
00:23:29.783 --> 00:23:33.787
Seeing him. the person who taught me
everything. dying. you know what I mean?

528
00:23:34.788 --> 00:23:37.249
When I was taking him
to the hospital one time. he was like.

529
00:23:37.332 --> 00:23:39.167
"I regret working so much."

530
00:23:39.251 --> 00:23:42.170
You know. "I wish I had more time
with the people I love."

531
00:23:42.254 --> 00:23:44.339
And that hit me. I'm like. "Damn."

532
00:23:44.423 --> 00:23:46.800
It made me feel like. you know.
I gotta be closer to family.

533
00:23:46.883 --> 00:23:47.884
[Hayley] Mm-hm.

534
00:23:48.385 --> 00:23:51.096
Wow. That's really good.

535
00:23:51.179 --> 00:23:54.850
-Good? I just told you my trauma.
-I got scared. [laughing]

536
00:23:54.933 --> 00:23:57.936
-"Comfort me." [laughing]
-You're like. "Oh. that's good." [laughs]

537
00:23:58.019 --> 00:23:59.563
Oh. sorry.

538
00:23:59.646 --> 00:24:04.943
I am feeling butterflies.
I was not expecting butterflies at all.

539
00:24:05.026 --> 00:24:06.778
-Your smile brightens my day.
-Aw.

540
00:24:06.862 --> 00:24:07.863
[tender pop music playing]

541
00:24:07.946 --> 00:24:11.867
♪ Calling me in. calling me close ♪

542
00:24:11.950 --> 00:24:15.454
♪ Fall into your gravity ♪

543
00:24:15.537 --> 00:24:17.372
[Hayley] I'm confused.

544
00:24:17.456 --> 00:24:21.877
I didn't think
that this was going to happen here.

545
00:24:22.502 --> 00:24:23.336
Whoa.

546
00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:28.675
♪ When we're falling
There's no need for talking ♪

547
00:24:28.758 --> 00:24:31.261
♪ You can keep me locked in ♪

548
00:24:31.344 --> 00:24:33.388
♪ Take it slow ♪

549
00:24:33.472 --> 00:24:36.183
♪ In your afterglow ♪

550
00:24:36.266 --> 00:24:37.142
[music fades]

551
00:24:37.225 --> 00:24:41.146
I put this chain on. looked in the mirror.
like. "Uh-oh. I kinda look like David."

552
00:24:41.813 --> 00:24:43.773
He's here in spirit for you.
You're welcome.

553
00:24:43.857 --> 00:24:45.150
Appreciate it. [laughs]

554
00:24:45.233 --> 00:24:47.986
Let's remove it.
No. I'm just kidding. [laughs]

555
00:24:48.069 --> 00:24:50.822
-That was too funny. The chain looks nice.
-Thank you. Thank you.

556
00:24:50.906 --> 00:24:52.908
-Yeah. You look good today.
-Thank you.

557
00:24:52.991 --> 00:24:54.743
-You're welcome.
-You're very pretty.

558
00:24:54.826 --> 00:24:56.620
-I need you to know that.
-I appreciate that.

559
00:24:56.703 --> 00:24:58.497
[tender music playing]

560
00:24:58.580 --> 00:24:59.873
[music turns lively]

561
00:24:59.956 --> 00:25:03.251
-As a child. would you consider…
-I've never gotten in trouble.

562
00:25:03.335 --> 00:25:05.003
-That was--
-I never got in trouble.

563
00:25:05.086 --> 00:25:08.924
If a teacher ever even raised
their voice near me. I would cry.

564
00:25:09.007 --> 00:25:11.718
-Like. I was…
-Were you like a goody-goody?

565
00:25:11.801 --> 00:25:13.553
-Yeah. Like…
-That's adorable.

566
00:25:13.637 --> 00:25:16.681
I've never gotten in trouble.
I'm a rule follower. I still am. but--

567
00:25:16.765 --> 00:25:20.101
-I still kind of get that vibe.
-Oh. you do? Okay. Thank you.

568
00:25:20.185 --> 00:25:21.770
-In a cute way. I promise.
-Okay.

569
00:25:21.853 --> 00:25:22.729
[music fades]

570
00:25:22.812 --> 00:25:25.774
We would not have gotten along as kids.

571
00:25:25.857 --> 00:25:28.068
-I get the vibe you're a class clown.
-100%.

572
00:25:28.902 --> 00:25:33.281
When I got the quiet goody to laugh
at my jokes. it meant the world. so…

573
00:25:33.365 --> 00:25:35.492
-Oh. good.
-If you were laughing. I'd love it.

574
00:25:35.575 --> 00:25:37.035
Would've made your day. Every day.

575
00:25:37.118 --> 00:25:39.704
It's a red flag if you didn't.
I'm not gonna lie. Gonna be honest.

576
00:25:39.788 --> 00:25:41.331
-Passed the test. Scary.
-That was close.

577
00:25:41.414 --> 00:25:42.290
-Close one.
-Really.

578
00:25:42.374 --> 00:25:44.084
-I know. God.
-Right on the edge.

579
00:25:44.167 --> 00:25:48.463
Don't put me there anymore. okay?
That's a close one. [laughing nervously]

580
00:25:48.547 --> 00:25:49.464
Just kidding.

581
00:25:49.548 --> 00:25:50.423
[gentle music playing]

582
00:25:50.507 --> 00:25:52.092
-No.
-Look it. Look it. Look it.

583
00:25:52.175 --> 00:25:54.302
-[Casey] I know. I just saw her.
-[laughs]

584
00:25:54.886 --> 00:25:57.222
-[Casey] Oh my goodness.
-That little dress.

585
00:25:57.305 --> 00:25:59.391
-I know.
-[Luke laughs]

586
00:25:59.474 --> 00:26:01.017
-You want kids?
-Oh. yeah.

587
00:26:01.101 --> 00:26:02.143
-Yeah?
-Oh. yeah.

588
00:26:02.227 --> 00:26:03.436
How soon do you want kids?

589
00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:06.273
-My answer to kids was always 30-31.
-Mm-hm.

590
00:26:06.356 --> 00:26:09.317
-Thinking I'd be married at 27-28.
-Mm-hm.

591
00:26:09.401 --> 00:26:12.028
So. now I'm 30.
Hopefully. getting married soon.

592
00:26:12.112 --> 00:26:12.988
Yeah.

593
00:26:13.697 --> 00:26:17.075
The idea is a couple years.
maybe a year. year and a half.

594
00:26:17.158 --> 00:26:20.412
-Be married first. Yeah.
-No kids. just be married for a while.

595
00:26:20.495 --> 00:26:22.831
-Enjoy life as married.
-That's exactly what I want. Yep.

596
00:26:23.999 --> 00:26:26.293
I also was born to be a mother.
I want to be a mother.

597
00:26:26.376 --> 00:26:29.170
-I can see you being a really good mom.
-Really? Thank you.

598
00:26:29.254 --> 00:26:31.047
-That same peaceness.
-That means a lot.

599
00:26:31.131 --> 00:26:33.633
I feel taken care of when I talk to you.

600
00:26:33.717 --> 00:26:35.927
so I can only imagine
how you'd treat a kid.

601
00:26:36.011 --> 00:26:38.138
That makes me feel really good.
I appreciate that.

602
00:26:38.221 --> 00:26:40.599
-Excuse me. Let me get those menus.
-Yeah. of course.

603
00:26:40.682 --> 00:26:42.851
[Luke] Do you have.
uh. crushed red pepper?

604
00:26:42.934 --> 00:26:44.811
-Yes. I do. I can bring you some.
-Thank you.

605
00:26:44.894 --> 00:26:46.313
You like it spicy?

606
00:26:46.396 --> 00:26:47.397
[Luke] Yeah.

607
00:26:47.480 --> 00:26:50.817
How do you want to raise kids?
Like. what does that look like for you?

608
00:26:50.900 --> 00:26:51.776
[Luke] Hm…

609
00:26:51.860 --> 00:26:54.613
-In one word. traditional.
-Okay.

610
00:26:54.696 --> 00:26:58.533
I do plan to introduce
the religion that I believe in

611
00:26:58.617 --> 00:27:02.162
and the God that I believe in
to my kids. but it's not…

612
00:27:02.245 --> 00:27:03.663
-Expected.
-It's not forced.

613
00:27:03.747 --> 00:27:07.167
I want them to know
that their life is theirs.

614
00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:09.461
-Mm-hm.
-What they want to do with it.

615
00:27:09.544 --> 00:27:13.298
-And we're here to help them do that.
-I wish there were more people like that.

616
00:27:13.381 --> 00:27:15.925
♪ I'm thinking today's the day ♪

617
00:27:16.009 --> 00:27:17.844
♪ Getting out of my way… ♪

618
00:27:17.927 --> 00:27:20.305
Every time I talk to Luke.
I like him more and more.

619
00:27:20.388 --> 00:27:23.600
Luke and I did both give
our ex-partners Ultimatums.

620
00:27:23.683 --> 00:27:26.811
and it's really attractive to me
that he knows what he wants.

621
00:27:26.895 --> 00:27:29.314
I just think we're seeing very eye to eye.

622
00:27:29.397 --> 00:27:30.440
-Yeah.
-On a lot of things.

623
00:27:30.523 --> 00:27:33.068
[Casey] David and I have been together
for over five years.

624
00:27:33.151 --> 00:27:34.944
so it's easy to feel complacent.

625
00:27:35.028 --> 00:27:36.363
But with Luke.

626
00:27:36.446 --> 00:27:39.157
he's a very glass-half-full.
bubbly personality.

627
00:27:39.240 --> 00:27:41.117
so every day is just always a good time.

628
00:27:41.201 --> 00:27:44.162
That's awesome. [laughs] Yeah.

629
00:27:44.245 --> 00:27:46.206
I feel very connected to you.

630
00:27:46.873 --> 00:27:47.791
Feels good.

631
00:27:47.874 --> 00:27:50.085
-Same.
-Okay. good.

632
00:27:50.669 --> 00:27:52.587
♪ This is the life I prayed for ♪

633
00:27:52.671 --> 00:27:54.631
♪ Knew I could find my place ♪

634
00:27:54.714 --> 00:27:58.259
♪ Finally found my way. oh ♪

635
00:27:58.343 --> 00:27:59.386
[music fades]

636
00:27:59.469 --> 00:28:01.554
-[Jessica Grace] You good here?
-[Luke] Yeah.

637
00:28:01.638 --> 00:28:04.391
-I was hoping you'd pick shade.
-And… Huh? Yeah.

638
00:28:04.474 --> 00:28:06.059
-[Luke] Have some mango.
-Is it good?

639
00:28:06.142 --> 00:28:08.144
-[Luke] It's real good.
-Can I eat off your spoon?

640
00:28:09.104 --> 00:28:12.524
-Okay. this was…
-It was very vanilla. [laughs]

641
00:28:13.441 --> 00:28:14.818
-I was happy.
-Listen.

642
00:28:14.901 --> 00:28:16.027
Nothing wrong with vanilla.

643
00:28:16.111 --> 00:28:18.988
as long as you like to mix it up
with a little chocolate too. Come on.

644
00:28:19.072 --> 00:28:23.201
Okay. what is that? "First Corinthians"?
That's what I was reading today.

645
00:28:23.284 --> 00:28:26.454
Really? It says. "When I was a child.
I thought like a child.

646
00:28:26.538 --> 00:28:28.331
acted like a child.
and reasoned like a child."

647
00:28:28.415 --> 00:28:30.542
"When I became a man.
I put childish things away."

648
00:28:30.625 --> 00:28:34.254
-Okay.
-This is a reminder of who I am deep down.

649
00:28:34.337 --> 00:28:36.297
Yeah. I like that a lot.

650
00:28:36.381 --> 00:28:42.303
I think that speaks to your ability
to be a good husband and partner.

651
00:28:42.887 --> 00:28:47.475
It's one of the most frustrating parts
of having to be here.

652
00:28:47.559 --> 00:28:51.813
having to put this Ultimatum on
because I don't want much.

653
00:28:51.896 --> 00:28:55.233
Like. I will do what it takes
to take care of you.

654
00:28:55.316 --> 00:28:57.652
So that's why
it's very frustrating to just. like--

655
00:28:57.736 --> 00:29:00.029
-I can tell my ex all that.
-[pensive music playing]

656
00:29:00.113 --> 00:29:02.282
And she would say. "Great."

657
00:29:02.365 --> 00:29:04.325
If you could figure out
your issues with Monica.

658
00:29:04.409 --> 00:29:05.952
and I figure out my issues with Edris…

659
00:29:06.035 --> 00:29:07.412
-We'd be at home.
-We'd be at home.

660
00:29:07.495 --> 00:29:11.958
Like. we-- Obviously. we're at this point
because we can't figure it out.

661
00:29:12.041 --> 00:29:14.335
I don't want to be alone.
That's why I'm here.

662
00:29:14.419 --> 00:29:16.296
You want to be chosen.

663
00:29:16.379 --> 00:29:19.591
I think that one of the things
that this is challenging is.

664
00:29:19.674 --> 00:29:25.889
how well do I love myself
with someone new? When I'm alone?

665
00:29:25.972 --> 00:29:31.227
And how will that affect
my ability to love a husband.

666
00:29:31.311 --> 00:29:33.396
like. at the end of all of this.

667
00:29:33.480 --> 00:29:35.774
whether it's my ex or not?

668
00:29:35.857 --> 00:29:36.691
[Luke] Hm.

669
00:29:36.775 --> 00:29:41.946
In a long-term relationship
where trust is not solid.

670
00:29:42.822 --> 00:29:46.242
it's really. really easy
to start doubting yourself.

671
00:29:46.326 --> 00:29:47.952
-I'm sure of that.
-Yeah.

672
00:29:48.036 --> 00:29:50.830
-Yeah. I agree.
-[poignant pop music playing]

673
00:29:50.914 --> 00:29:53.583
Oh. it's making me teary-eyed.
just like thinking about it.

674
00:29:54.167 --> 00:29:56.377
♪ We're in this together ♪

675
00:29:56.961 --> 00:29:58.463
♪ We're in this together ♪

676
00:29:58.546 --> 00:30:01.966
Yeah. just like.
my emotions have been all over the place.

677
00:30:02.050 --> 00:30:04.803
[Luke] Hey. it's okay. [laughs]

678
00:30:04.886 --> 00:30:09.724
♪ Never alone ♪

679
00:30:09.808 --> 00:30:12.101
-You deserve that love.
-Thank you.

680
00:30:15.438 --> 00:30:17.440
[music fades]

681
00:30:18.775 --> 00:30:20.777
♪ I feel like something new ♪

682
00:30:20.860 --> 00:30:21.903
[lively rap music playing]

683
00:30:21.986 --> 00:30:23.238
♪ Hello ♪

684
00:30:23.321 --> 00:30:25.990
♪ Whoa. hello. I think I like you ♪

685
00:30:26.074 --> 00:30:28.785
-♪ Ooh-la-la ♪
-♪ Yeah. whoa… ♪

686
00:30:29.369 --> 00:30:30.328
Hi!

687
00:30:30.411 --> 00:30:31.621
-Hello!
-What's up. ladies?

688
