00:40:22.711 --> 00:40:25.464
Yes. And the gorilla. the bear.
the skiing. and the snowboarding.

923
00:40:25.548 --> 00:40:29.718
[Alex] I can see how. like.
immature he is. the way that he acts.

924
00:40:29.802 --> 00:40:31.595
It's so hard. He's always joking.

925
00:40:31.679 --> 00:40:34.682
[Jessica Grace] Is Jebin showing up
that way because it's not in him.

926
00:40:34.765 --> 00:40:36.183
or because he just needs more time?

927
00:40:36.267 --> 00:40:38.936
-[Ashley] I think he needs to be pushed.
-I think he needs more time.

928
00:40:39.019 --> 00:40:40.229
[Ashley] He needs to be pushed.

929
00:40:40.312 --> 00:40:43.566
He needs to not live with his family.
he needs to be in a role as an adult.

930
00:40:43.649 --> 00:40:46.485
-Because he's lived at home.
-[Monica] He feels young.

931
00:40:46.569 --> 00:40:48.487
You feel so mature for your age.

932
00:40:48.571 --> 00:40:49.947
I know you gave The Ultimatum.

933
00:40:50.030 --> 00:40:54.034
but do you feel like if he didn't grow
in the ways that you needed him to.

934
00:40:54.118 --> 00:40:58.247
even if he was ready to propose.
if he wasn't there. like. emotionally.

935
00:40:58.330 --> 00:41:01.292
and maturity-wise. that you'd have
second thoughts yourself?

936
00:41:01.375 --> 00:41:02.668
[Alex] Yeah. for sure.

937
00:41:02.751 --> 00:41:07.506
I would have to just be like.
I can't… I don't see it.

938
00:41:07.590 --> 00:41:09.508
♪ I'm waiting for you ♪

939
00:41:09.592 --> 00:41:13.429
♪ I ain't never felt
The way I'm feeling for you… ♪

940
00:41:13.512 --> 00:41:14.597
[sultry rap music playing]

941
00:41:14.680 --> 00:41:16.140
You look good.

942
00:41:16.223 --> 00:41:18.350
Thank you. You always look good.

943
00:41:18.434 --> 00:41:21.520
-Thanks. What's good?
-[Jessica Grace] You tell me. babe.

944
00:41:21.604 --> 00:41:23.522
[Jebin] Just learning some stuff.

945
00:41:24.023 --> 00:41:26.025
Yeah? What do you think
you've learned the most?

946
00:41:26.108 --> 00:41:28.360
I don't know if it's. like. learned.

947
00:41:28.444 --> 00:41:31.572
I'm not giving you the right
to even express your needs.

948
00:41:31.655 --> 00:41:34.700
And it sucks that
that's. like. what I'm doing.

949
00:41:34.783 --> 00:41:35.743
[poignant music playing]

950
00:41:35.826 --> 00:41:40.414
And. like. trying to get to a point.
like. of a clean slate. if possible.

951
00:41:40.915 --> 00:41:44.502
-What does a clean slate look like?
-I wouldn't hold anything against you.

952
00:41:44.585 --> 00:41:49.340
♪ I've seen your eyes
But now I see them in my dreams… ♪

953
00:41:49.423 --> 00:41:53.219
Do you even want to
do the work with me to get there?

954
00:41:54.136 --> 00:41:58.390
I just feel like
forgiveness is so easy for me

955
00:41:58.474 --> 00:42:02.686
because I understand that it is a part of…

956
00:42:04.939 --> 00:42:06.440
love.

957
00:42:06.524 --> 00:42:07.399
Yeah.

958
00:42:07.483 --> 00:42:09.735
I mean. all of this is on your terms.

959
00:42:11.195 --> 00:42:12.196
Is it not?

960
00:42:13.906 --> 00:42:16.450
I mean. you got the ability
to walk away any moment too.

961
00:42:16.534 --> 00:42:18.118
Do you want me to?

962
00:42:18.202 --> 00:42:22.998
♪ You've heard my voice
But now you're distant in my sight… ♪

963
00:42:23.082 --> 00:42:25.292
I am genuinely

964
00:42:25.376 --> 00:42:30.214
wanting to spend
the rest of my life loving you.

965
00:42:30.297 --> 00:42:31.924
All of you.

966
00:42:32.007 --> 00:42:36.178
♪ If I lose you. I lose my fight… ♪

967
00:42:38.514 --> 00:42:39.765
[Jessica Grace sighs]

968
00:42:39.848 --> 00:42:42.726
I think about marriage and kids. like…

969
00:42:45.396 --> 00:42:46.355
it's you.

970
00:42:49.483 --> 00:42:52.695
This is torture. knowing that
you're connecting with other girls.

971
00:42:52.778 --> 00:42:54.989
knowing that you find them attractive.

972
00:42:55.072 --> 00:42:59.493
Yeah. if this is anything close
to what I made you feel.

973
00:43:00.369 --> 00:43:01.620
this is awful.

974
00:43:02.830 --> 00:43:04.206
[Edris] I don't know how you do it.

975
00:43:04.290 --> 00:43:08.669
You're listening to my mind.
and saying exactly what you need to say.

976
00:43:08.752 --> 00:43:11.672
It's not what--
I'm not trying to say what I need to say.

977
00:43:11.755 --> 00:43:14.466
I'm saying what I feel.
and if that is resonating with you.

978
00:43:14.550 --> 00:43:16.927
it's because we are connected. Edris.

979
00:43:18.762 --> 00:43:20.472
[music fades]

980
00:43:20.556 --> 00:43:21.932
Give me a kiss. please.

981
00:43:22.850 --> 00:43:24.226
No. bubba. a real one.

982
00:43:24.310 --> 00:43:25.144
[laughs]

983
00:43:25.227 --> 00:43:27.229
[tender R&B music playing]

984
00:43:28.522 --> 00:43:29.523
Every choice

985
00:43:30.566 --> 00:43:31.775
is choosing you.

986
00:43:31.859 --> 00:43:36.780
♪ Eyes locked tight
I can't get you out my mind. oh no… ♪

987
00:43:36.864 --> 00:43:40.242
You looking real good tonight. baby.
Your skin looking flawless.

988
00:43:40.326 --> 00:43:42.119
-I know.
-Your hair looking good.

989
00:43:42.202 --> 00:43:43.037
Yeah.

990
00:43:43.120 --> 00:43:45.289
What you been doing?
You been eating or something?

991
00:43:45.372 --> 00:43:47.249
-I haven't been eating. honestly.
-Really?

992
00:43:47.333 --> 00:43:49.043
-Breakfast. you know what you gotta get?
-Hm?

993
00:43:49.126 --> 00:43:51.503
What do you get?
You get Starbucks. don't you?

994
00:43:51.587 --> 00:43:52.838
-I get Starbucks.
-[laughing]

995
00:43:52.921 --> 00:43:55.716
I get a banana and coffee.

996
00:43:55.799 --> 00:43:57.968
No. you need to get. uh. steak and eggs.

997
00:43:58.052 --> 00:44:01.847
And then for lunch.
get steak and mashed potatoes.

998
00:44:01.930 --> 00:44:04.767
For dinner. steak and mashed potatoes
and mashed potatoes.

999
00:44:04.850 --> 00:44:05.768
[laughs]

1000
00:44:05.851 --> 00:44:09.521
You don't seem like you're taking it hard.
That's the thing. I mean. why?

1001
00:44:09.605 --> 00:44:12.191
-I mean. I have been.
-No. it doesn't seem like it.

1002
00:44:12.274 --> 00:44:13.400
No. I definitely have been.

1003
00:44:13.484 --> 00:44:19.782
The thing is. is that you don't get deep.
and I feel like you. like. joke too much.

1004
00:44:19.865 --> 00:44:23.619
Like. for me. my dates are.
like. very deep conversations.

1005
00:44:23.702 --> 00:44:26.622
-Half of it's deep. half of it's laughing.
-Jokey.

1006
00:44:26.705 --> 00:44:31.460
Yeah. but you need to show people
that you can be like that.

1007
00:44:31.543 --> 00:44:35.506
Because. I'm gonna be honest.
the girls literally tell me all the time.

1008
00:44:35.589 --> 00:44:37.383
like. you don't deserve me.

1009
00:44:37.466 --> 00:44:40.552
It makes me overthink.
and I'm like. "What am I doing then?"

1010
00:44:40.636 --> 00:44:44.390
-I also want you to be--
-Do you want to listen to them. or…?

1011
00:44:44.473 --> 00:44:47.309
No. I'm trying to listen.
like. to what I feel.

1012
00:44:47.393 --> 00:44:48.310
Yeah. I don't know.

1013
00:44:48.394 --> 00:44:51.563
I feel like if you're trying
to listen to other people.

1014
00:44:51.647 --> 00:44:55.275
and how they think you should feel. then…

1015
00:44:56.360 --> 00:44:59.405
I don't know why we even came here.

1016
00:44:59.488 --> 00:45:01.740
[tense music playing]

1017
00:45:02.533 --> 00:45:05.744
Here. I got something for you before.
Open up your purse.

1018
00:45:05.828 --> 00:45:07.830
[men chattering indistinctly]

1019
00:45:08.455 --> 00:45:09.915
[laughs]

1020
00:45:13.669 --> 00:45:15.963
-What is it?
-I want you to take this for after.

1021
00:45:16.046 --> 00:45:17.965
Aw. Thank you.

1022
00:45:18.465 --> 00:45:20.092
-How are you feeling?
-Good. Give me a hug.

1023
00:45:20.175 --> 00:45:21.468
-Like you don't know me.
-I know!

1024
00:45:21.552 --> 00:45:23.470
-Oh. you smell good.
-[David] Always.

1025
00:45:23.554 --> 00:45:25.347
-What do you wear?
-[David laughs] Burberry.

1026
00:45:25.431 --> 00:45:29.435
-Mmm. It's good.
-It's like a soft. discontinued one.

1027
00:45:29.518 --> 00:45:30.853
-It's very nice.
-Ooh!

1028
00:45:30.936 --> 00:45:32.896
-All right. that vintage. [laughs]
-Love it.

1029
00:45:32.980 --> 00:45:34.189
Love that vintage. don't you?

1030
00:45:34.273 --> 00:45:35.941
-You look great. It's fabulous.
-Absolutely.

1031
00:45:36.024 --> 00:45:38.026
Thank you. I wore red again.

1032
00:45:38.110 --> 00:45:39.653
-My favorite color?
-Your favorite.

1033
00:45:39.737 --> 00:45:41.488
[David] Yes. you did it on purpose.

1034
00:45:41.572 --> 00:45:45.951
-[Monica] Where do you want to sit?
-We can sit here and talk real quick.

1035
00:45:46.034 --> 00:45:46.952
[Monica] Okay.

1036
00:45:47.494 --> 00:45:48.787
Thank you.

1037
00:45:48.871 --> 00:45:52.458
It's definitely just feeling the heaviness
of The Choice tomorrow.

1038
00:45:52.541 --> 00:45:55.502
-Yeah. same. You and Hayley both top two.
-Mm.

1039
00:45:55.586 --> 00:45:57.671
[David] Hayley. me and her
grew up kind of similar.

1040
00:45:57.755 --> 00:45:59.381
-Mm-hm.
-So we have that connection.

1041
00:45:59.465 --> 00:46:01.842
-Me and you have everything in common.
-Yeah.

1042
00:46:01.925 --> 00:46:03.886
-Which is fun. right?
-Mm-hm.

1043
00:46:03.969 --> 00:46:05.387
Do I want to go down the route

1044
00:46:05.471 --> 00:46:08.015
of being similar.
same as the person again?

1045
00:46:08.098 --> 00:46:09.391
-Can that push you almost?
-Yeah.

1046
00:46:09.475 --> 00:46:12.686
Or do I want something
that I look for in a wife. for real?

1047
00:46:12.770 --> 00:46:14.438
You know what I mean? All the qualities?

1048
00:46:14.521 --> 00:46:16.690
Because you have a lot
of very great qualities.

1049
00:46:16.774 --> 00:46:19.359
-Thank you. Love that. [laughs]
-You know that.

1050
00:46:21.612 --> 00:46:24.364
Yeah. Definitely seeing
a little bit more maturity in you.

1051
00:46:24.448 --> 00:46:26.241
-Mm-hm. Yeah.
-Which I really like.

1052
00:46:26.325 --> 00:46:28.786
I can tell you're taking
this experience really seriously.

1053
00:46:28.869 --> 00:46:32.164
[dramatic. pensive music playing]

1054
00:46:33.332 --> 00:46:35.626
[Luke] There's a big connection
between Monica and David.

1055
00:46:35.709 --> 00:46:41.048
I knew giving her this ultimatum.
the choice was marry me or move on.

1056
00:46:41.131 --> 00:46:42.925
We know what's at stake.

1057
00:46:43.008 --> 00:46:47.012
It gets realer and realer
the longer we're here.

1058
00:46:47.095 --> 00:46:50.224
It gets closer to that moment of…

1059
00:46:50.307 --> 00:46:52.059
I could lose her.

1060
00:46:52.142 --> 00:46:54.144
[dramatic. pensive music continues]

1061
00:46:55.604 --> 00:46:59.024
♪ The end has come to life ♪

1062
00:47:01.068 --> 00:47:04.446
♪ Nothing like this before ♪

1063
00:47:06.031 --> 00:47:09.576
♪ We'll show you something different ♪

1064
00:47:13.205 --> 00:47:16.750
♪ Experience something new… ♪

1065
00:47:16.834 --> 00:47:21.088
[Monica] Going into The Choice tonight
just kind of hit me full force.

1066
00:47:21.171 --> 00:47:23.006
I'm here. I'm doing this.

1067
00:47:23.090 --> 00:47:24.925
There is no going back.

1068
00:47:25.008 --> 00:47:27.427
There's multiple people

1069
00:47:27.511 --> 00:47:30.556
that are good matches
for everyone out there.

1070
00:47:30.639 --> 00:47:33.308
I think that you can
fall in love multiple times.

1071
00:47:33.392 --> 00:47:36.603
-She made it down the stairs.
-I made it. No falls. [chuckles]

1072
00:47:36.687 --> 00:47:41.191
I am feeling confident in where I'm at.
and who I want to choose.

1073
00:47:41.275 --> 00:47:45.696
I am excited to take on this adventure
and see what comes of it.

1074
00:47:46.280 --> 00:47:49.157
♪ Take me where I've never been ♪

1075
00:47:53.161 --> 00:47:56.582
♪ To the edge and back again… ♪

1076
00:47:57.875 --> 00:48:02.629
[Luke] I hope Monica can't find
someone here that's a better fit for her.

1077
00:48:02.713 --> 00:48:06.675
But I do think
her eyes are open to that possibility.

1078
00:48:06.758 --> 00:48:08.135
But that's the big risk.

1079
00:48:08.218 --> 00:48:10.804
Having issued The Ultimatum.

1080
00:48:10.888 --> 00:48:14.725
I believe I deserve the marriage I want.
the kids I want.

1081
00:48:15.434 --> 00:48:17.895
-[Nick] What's up. Luke?
-Hey.

1082
00:48:18.478 --> 00:48:24.985
And if I can't get that from my ex.
then I have to find it from somebody else.

1083
00:48:25.068 --> 00:48:27.112
[dramatic. pensive music continues]

1084
00:48:27.195 --> 00:48:32.659
♪ Experience something new… ♪

1085
00:48:32.743 --> 00:48:36.413
[Alex] I gave my ex-partner
Jebin The Ultimatum.

1086
00:48:36.496 --> 00:48:42.294
But hearing the girls
talk about Jebin the way that they did.

1087
00:48:42.377 --> 00:48:44.296
some of the things I do agree with.

1088
00:48:44.379 --> 00:48:46.006
Yeah. he does have to grow up.

1089
00:48:46.089 --> 00:48:48.884
And then just meeting
all of the other men.

1090
00:48:48.967 --> 00:48:52.888
maybe Jebin isn't the person
that I'm going to spend my life with.

1091
00:48:53.639 --> 00:48:56.975
I'm feeling really confused and doubting.

1092
00:48:58.560 --> 00:49:01.688
♪ It's what we're living for ♪

1093
00:49:01.772 --> 00:49:03.023
[music fades]

1094
00:49:03.106 --> 00:49:06.693
Well. welcome. everybody.
officially. to The Choice.

1095
00:49:07.361 --> 00:49:11.073
I know it's been an eye-opening
and an emotional week for a lot of you.

1096
00:49:13.408 --> 00:49:19.039
Just one week ago.
you arrived here as six couples.

1097
00:49:19.122 --> 00:49:24.628
One person was ready to get married.
and the other. not so much.

1098
00:49:24.711 --> 00:49:27.714
-[Nick] You chose to accept an Ultimatum.
-[pensive music playing]

1099
00:49:28.715 --> 00:49:31.301
And you ended your previous relationships.

1100
00:49:32.427 --> 00:49:36.848
Now. it's very. very clear.
at this point. what's at stake.

1101
00:49:38.100 --> 00:49:39.726
[Vanessa] You're all now single.

1102
00:49:40.978 --> 00:49:43.522
Twelve individuals.

1103
00:49:44.690 --> 00:49:46.692
With a common goal in mind.

1104
00:49:47.317 --> 00:49:50.320
You are all interested in being married.

1105
00:49:51.154 --> 00:49:53.115
But the question is.

1106
00:49:53.198 --> 00:49:57.202
did you come here with the person that
you'll spend the rest of your life with.

1107
00:49:57.285 --> 00:50:02.249
or is someone else a better fit?

1108
00:50:03.750 --> 00:50:04.751
[music fades]

1109
00:50:04.835 --> 00:50:06.545
But before we get into all of that.

1110
00:50:07.129 --> 00:50:11.550
we need to discuss some details
from last night's cocktail party.

1111
00:50:11.633 --> 00:50:16.471
We were made aware
of a note that was passed last night.

1112
00:50:16.555 --> 00:50:17.931
[suspenseful music playing]

1113
00:50:19.558 --> 00:50:23.186
Alex. I believe you received a note.

1114
00:50:23.270 --> 00:50:25.439
-[Alex] Yeah.
-[Nick] Who passed you that note?

1115
00:50:25.522 --> 00:50:26.732
[Alex] Jebin.

1116
00:50:26.815 --> 00:50:30.152
And the producers
actually took it from me.

1117
00:50:30.235 --> 00:50:31.695
I didn't read any of it.

1118
00:50:31.778 --> 00:50:33.155
We actually have the note.

1119
00:50:34.656 --> 00:50:36.408
♪ Adrenaline ♪

1120
00:50:36.992 --> 00:50:38.660
♪ Heart pumping ♪

1121
00:50:38.744 --> 00:50:42.164
♪ Feel it in your bones ♪

1122
00:50:42.247 --> 00:50:45.167
Communication is paramount
in this entire experience.

1123
00:50:45.250 --> 00:50:46.251
You all are aware of that.

1124
00:50:46.334 --> 00:50:47.753
But that communication.

1125
00:50:47.836 --> 00:50:50.172
frankly. needs to happen on camera.

1126
00:50:50.255 --> 00:50:51.548
That's part of this experience.

1127
00:50:51.631 --> 00:50:55.343
that's part of what
makes this entire process unique.

1128
00:50:55.427 --> 00:50:57.054
So we have the note.

1129
00:50:57.137 --> 00:51:00.932
I'd love to give you an opportunity
to read the note out loud.

1130
00:51:02.392 --> 00:51:03.935
♪ Watch out ♪

1131
00:51:04.019 --> 00:51:05.979
♪ It's coming ♪

1132
00:51:06.063 --> 00:51:07.731
♪ You can't escape it ♪

1133
00:51:07.814 --> 00:51:09.900
This is what you got yourself into.

1134
00:51:11.902 --> 00:51:16.323
♪ Step into a new world ♪

1135
00:51:16.406 --> 00:51:17.991
[suspenseful music swelling]

1136
00:51:23.038 --> 00:51:27.084
♪ Step into a new world ♪

1137
00:51:27.167 --> 00:51:32.589
♪ There's a hush in my footsteps ♪

1138
00:51:32.672 --> 00:51:34.591
[dramatic music playing]

1139
00:51:34.674 --> 00:51:39.096
♪ Nothing heard. nothing seen ♪

1140
00:51:42.182 --> 00:51:47.270
♪ Looking right before I look left ♪

1141
00:51:49.689 --> 00:51:54.111
♪ Resonance in the breeze ♪

1142
00:51:56.655 --> 00:51:58.115
♪ Sound ♪

1143
00:51:59.950 --> 00:52:01.118
[music fades]

